# id: AssignerWithPunctuatedWatermarks -> Watermark checkAndGetNextWatermark(T lastElement, long extractedTimestamp)_
commentText:
Asks this implementation if it wants to emit a watermark. This method is called right after_the {@link #extractTimestamp(Object, long)} method. If the method returns a positive_value, a new watermark should be emitted. If a negative value is emitted, no new watermark_will be generated.__

Note that whenever this method returns a positive value that is larger than the previous_value, a new watermark is generated. Hence, the implementation has full control how often_watermarks are generated.__

For an example how to use this method, see the documentation of_{@link AssignerWithPunctuatedWatermarks this class}.__@return {@code Null}, if no watermark should be emitted, or the next watermark to emit.

# id: AssignerWithPunctuatedWatermarks -> Watermark checkAndGetNextWatermark(T lastElement, long extractedTimestamp)_
commentText:
Asks this implementation if it wants to emit a watermark. This method is called right after_the {@link #extractTimestamp(Object, long)} method.__

The returned watermark will be emitted only if it is non-null and its timestamp_is larger than that of the previously emitted watermark (to preserve the contract of_ascending watermarks). If a null value is returned, or the timestamp of the returned_watermark is smaller than that of the last emitted one, then no new watermark will_be generated.__

For an example how to use this method, see the documentation of_{@link AssignerWithPunctuatedWatermarks this class}.__@return {@code Null}, if no watermark should be emitted, or the next watermark to emit.
